						<div class="postbody">I pretty much agree with rainwarrior on every point he made.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">DO NOT PUT YOUR OWN WORDS IN THEIR MOUTH, EVEN IF YOU THINK IT'S WHAT THEY MEANT.</div><br />Should I take this as implying that it's polite to reply publicly to what a user said, even if I know it is not what the user meant?</div><br />As far as I can tell, that's called being a smart-ass, and many people don't appreciate that. If you think something is ambiguous, the polite thing to do would probably be to ask the poster what he meant, possibly offering reworded alternatives for HIM to choose whether to make your words his.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Do I need to leave for a while?</div><br />Why? Just don't go editing people's posts based on OCD rather than actual necessity. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" /></div>

